8. The Storm Riders   2/7/1956
A rancher named John Dembro gives shelter to Cheyenne who&#039;s been hurt in an "incident" on the adjoining ranch owned by Martin Storm. Both Dembro&#039;s teenaged daughter, Johnny, and her stepmother, Sheila, are anxious to treat Cheyenne&#039;s injuries and they become bitter rivals.
  Guest star: Lane Bradford (Hadley), Mickey Simpson (Swallow) , Howard Negley (Ed Jeffries), Paul E. Burns (Marty), Beverly Michaels (Sheila Dembro), Regis Toomey (Dembro), Anne Whitfield (Johnny Dembro), Barton McLane (Storm)

9. Rendezvous at Red Rock   2/21/1956
Pat Keogh is a bank robber and killer who, when the episode begins, has just killed a man and Cheyenne has been accused by a group of vigilantes. Keogh rescues Cheyenne, admitting to him that he was the guilty party, and he cuts Cheyenne in on the bank robbery he&#039;s about to make in Red Rock with the help of two accomplices.
  Guest star: Gerald Mohr (Pat Keogh), Leo G. Carroll, Dawn Richard (Mille), Joel Ashley (Clayton), David Alpert (Chad), Helene Marshall (Joan), Sam Flint (Roberts), John Cliff (Turner), Steve Darrell (Grayson), Douglas Fowley (Pritchard)
